Domestic and farm-animal exposures and risk of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma in a population-based study in the San Francisco Bay Area. To assess the association between animal exposures and non-Hodgkin's lymphoma (NHL).Exposure data were collected from 1,591 cases and 2,515 controls during in-person interviews in a population-based case-control study of NHL in the San Francisco Bay Area. Odds ratios (OR) and 95% confidence intervals (95% CI) were adjusted for potential confounders.Pet owners had a reduced risk of NHL (OR, 0.71 95% CI, 0.52-0.97) and diffuse large-cell lymphoma large cell (DLCLThe association between animal exposure and NHL warrants further investigation in pooled analyses.